"I've seen tons of resumes. Here are some common pitfalls I've seen:\n\n1️⃣ Overloading with Text: Keep it clean and concise. Highlight your top achievements instead of listing every responsibility individually.\n\n2️⃣ Skipping Keywords: Tailor your resume to the job by using keywords from the posting. Yes, this is an extra step, but it's worth it.\n\n3️⃣ Generic Summaries: Customize your summary to show how you bring unique value to the role that you're applying for.\n\n4️⃣ Ignoring Metrics: Use numbers to show impact. For example: ""Increased efficiency by 30%"" is much stronger than ""Improved processes.""\n\n5️⃣ Formats: Resumes should be sleek and ATS-friendly. Stick to a design that’s easy to read.\n\nFollow, Connect or DM for more. 🚀\n\nWhat are your biggest resume pet peeves? Drop them in the comments—I’d love to hear! 👇\n\n…more"
