"Your resume gets 6 seconds. \n\nSIX SECONDS. That’s all recruiters need...\n\nTo decide if your CV lands\nin the “no thanks” pile.\n\nIf your resume is sending the wrong signals,\nit’s game over—before you’ve even started.\n\nHere’s how to fix it fast:\n\n1. ""I Didn’t Read the Job Posting.""\n🔴 Red Flag: Clichés like “detail-oriented” or “team player.”\n🟢 Fix It: Mirror the job description. Use keywords and highlight specific achievements.\n\n2. ""I’m Living in the Past.""\n🔴 Red Flag: Listing ancient or irrelevant experience.\n🟢 Fix It: Focus on the last 10 years. Keep it lean & relevant.\n\n3. ""I’m Afraid of Technology.""\n🔴 Red Flag: No mention of tools or platforms.\n🟢 Fix It: Add your tech stack—Excel, Salesforce, or certifications. Digital fluency is mandatory.\n\n4. ""I’m Hiding Something.""\n🔴 Red Flag: Unexplained employment gaps.\n🟢 Fix It: Fill the gaps—showcase freelancing, volunteering, or upskilling. Control the narrative.\n\n5. ""I Don’t Sweat the Details.""\n🔴 Red Flag: Typos, inconsistent formatting, outdated info.\n🟢 Fix It: Use Grammarly. Polished resumes show you care.\n\n6. ""I Have No Results to Show.""\n🔴 Red Flag: Vague phrases like “managed a team” or “responsible for projects.”\n🟢 Fix It: Quantify everything:\n“Boosted sales by 25%” > “Managed a team.”\n\n7. ""I’m Just Sending This Everywhere.""\n🔴 Red Flag: Generic resumes sent to every job.\n🟢 Fix It: Highlight wins that match the job description.\n\n8. ""I’m Desperate.""\n🔴 Red Flag: Applying for every job under the sun.\n🟢 Fix It: Stay focused. Align your resume to roles that tell one clear story.\n\n🔥 Your Resume = Your Pitch.\n\nIf it’s not selling your story,\nit’s time for a rewrite.\n\nWhat is your resume really saying about you?\n\n♻️ Share this to help someone today!\n🔔 And followfor more.\n…more"
