"Wrote a client's resume today. 📝\n\nMost people overthink this step, but after writing thousands of resumes, I’ve learned a few counterintuitive truths.\n\nHere are 3 quick contrarian resume writing tips:\n\n1️⃣ Write less, not more. Hiring managers skim. The more you write, the less they retain.\n2️⃣ You are less important than the company’s needs. Your resume isn’t about you—it’s about how you solve their problems.\n3️⃣ Stop trying to make it look pretty. Fancy designs don’t get jobs. Clear, scannable formatting does.\n\nHope that’s helpful.\n…more"
