"👀 Is Your Resume Easy to Read?\n\nAfter you’ve created your resume, take a moment to visually inspect it. Why? Because if it’s hard to read or navigate, it might not get the attention it deserves. Here’s a quick checklist to ensure it stands out:\n🔍 Top-to-Bottom Flow\nDoes your resume naturally guide the reader’s eye from the top of the page to the bottom and eventually landing on the experience section? That’s the most critical part—if it’s hard to find, you’re doing yourself a disservice.\n\n📂 Key Details at a Glance\nCan someone quickly spot your job titles, company names, and employment dates? Recruiters and hiring managers prioritize this information when evaluating your experience. Use different font sizes, bold and spacing to differential the info on your resume.\n\n🎯 Communicating Accomplishments\nDoes your resume highlight impact and relevance, or is it just a list of responsibilities? Think about the moments you’d proudly share during a performance review or promotion discussion. Those should be your first and second bullet points under every role.\n\n💡 Pro Tip\nIf your company is not well known, use one sentance to describe what the company does/industry it's in. It's one of the most common questions hiring managers have when reviewing a resume. ""What's that company do?""\n\n…more"
"Recently, I reviewed a resume so GOOD, it made me pause in the middle of my lunch & call the candidate to schedule an interview.\n\nIt wasn't just the layout or the fancy font that caught my eye; it was the clear, concise way the candidate's achievements and experiences were presented.\n\nIt was evident they had done their homework, tailoring their resume specifically for the role, making it impossible to ignore.\n\nSo, what's the recipe for a standout resume? 📄✨\n\n1. 𝐂𝐮𝐬𝐭𝐨𝐦𝐢𝐳𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐢𝐬 𝐊𝐞𝐲: Don't send out a one-size-fits-all resume. Tailor it to the job you're applying for, highlighting the experience and skills that align with the job description.\n\n\n2. 𝐂𝐥𝐚𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐲 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐜𝐢𝐬𝐞𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬: Keep it clear and to the point. Use bullet points to break down your achievements and make them easy to read.\n\n\n3. 𝐍𝐮𝐦𝐛𝐞𝐫𝐬 𝐒𝐩𝐞𝐚𝐤 𝐋𝐨𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐫: Quantify your achievements. Increased sales by 20%? Reduced project delivery times by 30%? These figures grab attention.\n\n\n4. 𝐀𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐭𝐢𝐜 𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐬: Choose a clean, professional template that makes your resume easy on the eyes. But remember, simplicity doesn't mean boring.\n\n\n5. 𝐏𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐟𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝, 𝐓𝐡𝐞𝐧 𝐏𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐟𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝 𝐀𝐠𝐚𝐢𝐧: Typos and grammatical errors can be the kiss of death for your application. Double-check, then have someone else check too.\n\n𝐀𝐧𝐝 𝐢𝐟 𝐲𝐨𝐮'𝐫𝐞 𝐰𝐨𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐰𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐫𝐭, 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐟𝐚𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐜 𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐜𝐞𝐬 𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞.\n\n✅ Its simple math, you need the job >> you got to demonstrate why you're the perfect fit for the role.\n\nSo, take that extra time to craft a resume that reflects the best version of you. It might just be the reason you land your dream job. 💼🌈\n\nFollowFor More!\n…more"
