"🕒 How I Review 100 Resumes in Under an Hour\n\nEver felt buried under a mountain of resumes? It’s easy to get overwhelmed, but there’s a faster, smarter way to sift through the noise and find the top talent. Here’s how I break it down:\n\n1️⃣ Prioritize must-have skills: Start with non-negotiables. If the role requires Python or AWS experience, filter for it upfront.\n\n2️⃣ Scan for relevant projects: Look for real-world examples where candidates contributed to projects similar to what you need.\n\n3️⃣ Check for career progression: Promotions, increased responsibility, and diverse roles show growth and initiative.\n\n4️⃣ Use keyword searches: Boolean search is your friend! Combine terms like “DevOps AND CI/CD” to narrow the pool.\n\n5️⃣ Pre-set scorecards: Create a scoring system to stay objective. Rate candidates based on skills, experience, and key achievements. No more gut-feeling decisions!\n\n⚡ Pro Tip: Batch your review time—30 focused minutes beats hours of multitasking any day.\n\nNeed a breakdown of any of these steps? Let me know!👇\n\n…more"
