"Building Your Resume ,the basics for the Undergrads\n\nKey Elements\n1.   Correct and Concise Information\no Ensure all information is accurate.\no Keep descriptions brief and to the point.\n2.   Clear Font and Format\no Use easy-to-read fonts (e.g., Arial, Calibri).\no Maintain consistent formatting (headings, bullet points).\n3.   Showcase Skills\no Highlight relevant skills at the top.\no Use a mix of hard and soft skills.\n4.   Project Achievements\no Include specific examples of projects.\no Use metrics to quantify achievements (e.g., “Increased sales by 20%”).\n5.   Sight on Keywords\no Use keywords from the job description.\no Incorporate industry-specific terms.\n6.   Efforts and Experience\no Detail your work experience clearly.\no Focus on responsibilities and contributions.\n\nBefore You Apply for a Job\n1.   Research About the Company\no Understand the company’s mission and values.\no Familiarize yourself with their products/services.\n2.   Update Resume\no Tailor your resume for each job application.\no Add any new skills or experiences.\n3.   Align Skills with Job Roles\no Highlight skills that match the job description.\no Use examples that demonstrate those skills.\n4.   Read Job Description Well\no Identify key responsibilities and requirements.\no  Ensure your resume addresses these points.\nAdditional Tips\n·      Proofread: Check for grammatical errors and typos.\n·      Keep it Relevant: Focus on experiences that relate to the job.\n·      Use Action Verbs: Start bullet points with strong action verbs (e.g., ""Developed,"" ""Led,"" ""Implemented"").\n…more"
