"Jeff Nevez, here with APC! I've seen countless resumes pass my desk. Unfortunately, some don’t make it to the next step for common, avoidable reasons. Here's what might be holding yours back:\n\n🔑 Lack of Relevant Experience\nIf your experience doesn't align with the job, recruiters may move on. Tailor your resume to highlight the most relevant skills and achievements.\n\n📝 Poor Resume Formatting\nA cluttered or difficult-to-read resume can be a dealbreaker. Stick to a clean format with clear headings and bullet points.\n\n📚 Missing Keywords\nApplicant Tracking Systems (ATS) scan for specific keywords. If they’re missing, your resume may be filtered out before anyone sees it.\n\n⏳ Employment Gaps Without Explanation\nGaps happen, and that’s okay—but explain them. Highlight growth during these periods, whether through learning, caregiving, or volunteering.\n\n🎯 Generic Objective Statements\nOutdated or vague objectives don’t help. Use a strong professional summary to show your value upfront.\n\n🔍 Typos and Grammar Errors\nMistakes show a lack of attention to detail. Double-check or ask someone to review it for you.\n\n⚠️ Inconsistent or Inaccurate Information\nInconsistent job titles or inflated claims raise red flags. Honesty is key.\n\n📊 Lack of Measurable Achievements\nJust listing job duties isn’t enough. Show your impact using numbers, percentages, and results.\n\n💡 By addressing these points, you’ll significantly increase your chances of getting noticed. Want more resume tips or career advice? Let’s connect!\n\nWhat’s your biggest challenge when it comes to resumes? Drop your thoughts below or shoot me a message!\n…more"
