"“Productive Perspective” #11\n\n❌Common Resume Mistakes That Can Get You Rejected Instantly!\n\nAs a\nreviewing countless resumes daily, I still see candidates making these avoidable mistakes. Here are some key reasons why resumes get rejected at first glance:\n\n1. Grammatical & Spelling Errors – A resume full of typos reflects a lack of attention to detail. Proofread carefully or use tools like Grammarly.\n\n2. Listing Every Possible Tool & Technology – Don’t just add all buzzwords to get a call. Only mention technologies you have actual hands-on experience with.\n\n3. Over-Reliance on AI-Generated Resumes – Using AI (like ChatGPT) to refine your resume is fine, but copying generic content can make it sound impersonal and irrelevant to your real experience.\n\n4. Frequent Job Hopping Without Explanation – If your resume shows job changes every few months or years, it raises red flags for recruiters. Address it in your profile summary if needed.\n\n5. Vague One-Word Responsibilities – Writing generic words like “Implementation,” “Development,” or “Support” for every project doesn’t help. Be specific about your contributions.\n\n6. Missing Project Durations & Education Year – Always mention the timeline for each project and your education year to avoid confusion about experience level.\n\nWant to stand out? Avoid these mistakes and craft a resume that truly reflects your skills and experience!\n\n🤔Did i miss on something?\n🗣️Share your views..\n\n…more"
