"When I started looking for a job, people said I should apply to a lot of them. But it didn't work out that way. I applied to many jobs and often got no response.\n\nWhy? Because when we rush, we sometimes miss important details about what the job needs. It's like trying to hit a target without looking.\n\nInstead of applying to tons of jobs randomly, it's better to focus on a few. Take time to understand what the job is about and what the company wants. Then, change your resume to match that. Make it fit what the company is looking for.\n\nIt's not about sending out a bunch of resumes—it's about sending the right ones. Quality is more important than quantity. If you match your resume with the job, you're more likely to get a call.\n\nSo, don't worry about applying everywhere. It's not a race. Take your time, understand the job, and then make your move. It's about being smart, not just being fast.\n\n…more"
